```
NonVariadicDotDotDot occurs when a "..." is used on the final argument to
a non-variadic function.

Example:
 func printArgs(s []string) {
 	for _, a := range s {
 		println(a)
 	}
 }

 func f() {
 	s := []string{"a", "b", "c"}
 	printArgs(s...)
 }
```
